description: The ruins of a Phoenician colony are recovered in Zaire, where Martin and Java arrive with an archaeological expedition. Some macabre discoveries lead them to believe that the colony was exterminated by an unknown virus that could still be active. Indirect confirmation is given by the interest the Men in Black take in the event. But the tragic confirmation to this theory comes from an epidemic of insane murders that spreads among the members of the expedition…
name: Il Nemico Invisible

description:
For mature readers only.

Stories contained within are:

  • Mid-Life Crisis
  • Wayne
  • Business as Usual
  • Annie the Avenging Secretary

Sociopath is an Ashcan sized comic book.

volume.name: Roy Rogers e o Trigger: Suplemento ao Mundo de Aventuras

deck: Tarzan Adventures was a British weekly series that consisted of reprinted comics strips, original stories and text pieces.
description:
Canvas and Wire by Moorcock

Tarzan Club: The Art of Burne Hogarth part 8 (written as Bob Lumley)

The risk of spreading of the epidemic that has broken out among the Phoenician ruins of Zaire is avoided by the intervention of a team from the Elsewhere base. Together with these agents, Martin discovers the origin of the archaeovirus that has struck his expedition. Once this African story has been concluded, it is time for a new Italian adventure for Mystère, who finds himself right in the middle of the Battle of San Romano (1432) near Florence.

In this number: From page 5 to Page 52, “Il nemico invisibile”, subject by Beretta, Gajo, Gandolfi, script by Beretta and artwork by Devescovi, From page 53, “I Cavalieri di San Romano”, Subject by Strufaldi, script by Strufaldi and Recano, artwork by Torti.
name: I cavalieri di San Romano

description:
The adventure where Martin finds himself trapped in a painting by Paolo Uccello “The battle of San Romano” ends . Then, there begins the story that throws light on the past of the Mystère lineage and the origins of their unusual surname. It all begins with a visit by the Detective of the Impossible to his great-uncle of whose existence he was actually completely unaware: Paul Mystère, unusually lively for his venerable age…

In this number: from page 5 to page 46, “I Cavalieri di San Romano”, artwork by Torti. From page 47, “Affari di Famiglia”, by Castelli and Alessandrini.
name: Affari di Famiglia

description: Martin and Java are guests of his uncle, Paul Mystère, in his ancient mansion in the heart of old England. Here they are able to discover part of the Mystère’s obscure family history. We find out how the Mystères owe their name to Docteur Mystère, an ingenious and adventurous Indian nobleman, the protagonist of a extraordinary serialized novel by the French writer Paul D’Ivoi!
name: Docteur Mystère

description: There are tattoos with great magic powers, like those that decorate the bodies of the “The nomads from the steppe”, an ancient Siberian population. Visiting an art exhibition on tattoos in New York, Mystère meets the archaeologist Jeremy Parker, who is very interested in one of the tattoos on show: it is on a shred of skin taken from the Pazyryk Mummy. However, some other mysterious characters are also interested in the relic that is usually exhibited at the Ermitage museum in St. Petersburg…
name: Lo spirito del tatuaggio

description: The hunt for the tattooed piece of skin from the Pazyryk Mummy continues. Martin is searching for the archaeologist Jeremy Parker, who has disappeared together with the precious relic from the “Nomads from the Steppe”. Leaving the United States for Russia, Mystère has to deal with the men paid by a Japanese organisation. The detective of the Impossible follows the trail of the tattoo to the freezing snow of Siberia where the adventure concludes.
name: L'ultimo nomade

description: Ireland. In a cave in Ross Carbery, Martin discovers an ancient amphora whose mysterious content, The Gift of the Gods, was stolen in 1912 by some archaeologists. The object was then loaded onto the “Titanic” and was therefore lost in the historic wreck. However now, an unknown ship which is identical to the sunk transatlantic liner docks in the port of New York…
name: Il Gigante Sommerso

description: New York. A wounded woman knocks at Martin Mystère’s door, asking for help. A little later, a gang of killers storms the house, forcing the Detective of the Impossible to run along with the mysterious woman. It’s the beginning of a tumultuous escape that takes them around the city, with the killers fast on their tracks. Who are those strange hunters, and what do they want from her? Is it just a coincidence that she came to 3, Washington Mews? Martin is unwillingly involved in the realization of a plan whose preparation took centuries, an enigma enclosed in the word "Tzadik". Who are the Thirty-six Righteous People? Maybe the answer can be found only in the fabulous city of Agarthi…
name: I trentasei giusti

deck: A series of short stories featuring Frankenstein.
name: Vol 2 #5

description:
Sanctuary was once a serene city...

...Until the king and queen were murdered. At once, the land erupted into chaos.

With one princess in exile and the other serving as little more than a figurehead. Sanctuary is now run by Geoffrey a cunning servant with ambitions to usurp the Throne... If he only can eliminate the rightful heirs.

When an overzealous young adventurer and a vicious pixie warrior discover the truth about Geoffrey's plan, they must choose - do they risk their lives to save te queen or sell their souls for the promise of fortune?

Filled with frightening monsters, beautiful pixies, and a rich world based on Sony Online Entertainment's virtual phenomenon.

This first chapter in the free realms adventure is sure to take you on a thrill ride!
name: Book One

description: A 28 page full-colour comic featuring renowned British physicist Prof. Brian Cox, and his adventures through space and time. Join him to explore the furthest reaches of our universe and ponder its intricacies with a manner in which only a brilliant British polymath could.

volume.name: The Interstellar Adventures of Professor Brian Cox

description: Year 1859: the effects of a sunstorm are felt on the Earth. Northern Lights appear in different areas of the world; the telegraphs run amok and stop working. December 2012: on the surface of the Sun, a new storm begins, more powerful of the one before, threatening to cause a telecommunication breakdown on a global level, rendering useless cell phones, satellites, GPS, radars. It could be the end of the civilization as we know it, and a group of expert from different areas is put in a safe place in advance, just in case... One of them is Martin Mystère...
name: La Fine del Mondo
The Dream Team, Steppin' Out, and The Baby and "The Babe"
Glad to be Mad... and That Ain't Bad, Earth to Mom!, and Nothin' But Net: A Romance
Flip-Flop at the Flap, The Hard Truth, and Dutch Treat

volume.name: Roy Rogers e o Trigger: Suplemento ao Mundo de Aventuras

description:
Curiosity and transphobia collide in the latest volume of Fantagraphics' critically acclaimed manga about a boy who wants to be a girl, and a girl who wants to be a boy.

In Volume 8, Nitori-kun, a boy who wants to be a girl, explores kissing with girlfriend Anna-chan; and Yoshino-san, a girl who wants to be a boy, finds the courage to go to school wearing a boy's uniform. Meanwhile, one of their male classmates, Doi-kun, who has caused our protagonists misery in the past, becomes intrigued with their grown-up friend Yuki-san, a transwoman. But Nitori-kun finds himself strangely drawn to Doi-kun…

Shimura Takako's Wandering Son has been rightly hailed as one of the most progressive and enlightened treatments of gender identity in the history of comics. The eighth volume continues to explore the lives of its characters with insight and sensitivity.

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 58: Spring
  • Chapter 59: The Opposite of "Like"
  • Chapter 60: The Measure of a Big Sister
  • Chapter 61: Wavering
  • Chapter 62: Live to Sing
  • Chapter 63: The Morning of a New Journey
  • Chapter 64: The Dam
  • Chapter 65: The Dam Bursts
  • Bonus Manga
